Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Install Python, pip, rsync and pytest
    apt-get update -y
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        rsync \
        ca-certificates
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare initial filesystem state expected by the automated tests
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------

    # Create the base user directory tree.
    mkdir -p /home/user/docs_working
    mkdir -p /home/user/production_docs
    mkdir -p /home/user/sync_logs

    # Populate /home/user/production_docs with the two required files.
    printf 'Old content\n'   > /home/user/production_docs/introduction.md
    printf 'remove me\n'     > /home/user/production_docs/obsolete.txt

    # Ensure the student (non-root runtime user) can freely modify all
    # working directories and their contents during the exercise.
    chmod -R 777 /home/user/docs_working /home/user/production_docs /home/user/sync_logs

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Nothing special needed; rely on container’s default environment.

%labels
    Author="Generated by ChatGPT"
    Description="Environment for the documentation sync task – includes pytest and the required initial filesystem state."

%help
    This Apptainer image is set up for the “local-vs-remote documentation sync”
    exercise.  It provides:
      • Python 3 and pytest (pre-installed)
      • rsync utility
      • Pre-created directories:
          /home/user/docs_working        (empty)
          /home/user/production_docs     (contains introduction.md & obsolete.txt)
          /home/user/sync_logs           (empty)
    Students can run tests with:   pytest -q